<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-778-016  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 778 016.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  June 19 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Identix to help produce smart/biometric terminal.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Blankenhorn, Dana.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Identix Inc. (research).andO;Ticker:    IDXX.andO;Topic:     Security SystemsSmart cardsBiometricsOn-Line Transaction Processing.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>IDENTIX TO HELP PRODUCE SMART CARD/BIOMETRIC TERMINAL SUNNYVALE, CALIFORNIA,U.S.A., 1990 JUN 15 (NB) -- Identix, which specializes in fingerprintidentification systems, will work with Groupe Bull of France and ASCOM AG ofSwitzerland on adapting that technology, along with so-called &quot;smart cards,&quot;into a foolproof transaction system.andM;Smart cards, which embed computer chips in plastic, can store much moreinformation on their holders than the magnetic-striped credit cards usedworldwide, but the technology has had difficulty making headway because itcosts so much, $4 against 10 cents for mag-stripes, and the cost ofconverting the world's credit card systems to accept the chips.andP;  In order tomake that conversion worthwhile, the smart card makers are hoping to createnew added values, like a foolproof identity system for credit card holders.andM;The Identix agreement calls for the development and marketing of transactionterminals utilizing Bull smart card readers supplied by its Spanishmanufacturing subsidiary, TELESINCRO, and 5,000 Identix biometric fingerprintrecognition system supplied through its European partner, ASCOM.andM;&quot;You can use it in a number of ways, not only for transactions but forverifying medical records,&quot; said Identix spokesman Randy Hawks.andP;  &quot;The retailapplication will likely be the last one implemented.andP;  Specialized marketswill come first.&quot;andM;The concept behind the products is to store personal identificationinformation, including digital fingerprint data, on the smart card.andP;  TheIdentix fingerprint recognition device, built into the transaction terminal,will instantly confirm the identity of the individual by comparing the actualfingerprint with that stored digitally in the smart card.andP;  The terminalswould be used in retail credit applications, portable identification systems,and for access control.andM;(Dana Blankenhorn/19900615/Press Contact: Identix, Randy Hawks, 408-739-2000)</TEXT></DOC>